title: Drone flies over Lake Oroville Auxiliary Spillway
text: Drone flies over Lake Oroville Auxiliary Spillway Feb 13, 2017 Approximately 188,000 people were evacuated due to the threat of the emergency spillway of the Oroville Dam, the United States' tallest dam, failing and unleashing flood waters. Here's drone footage from the California Department of Water Resources taken on Feb. 11, 2017 at 4 PM.
